==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[cacophonie]], from Greek [[κακοφωνία]], from [[κακός]] ‘bad’ + [[φωνή]] ‘sound’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kəˈkɒfəni/}} ''(UK)''
*{{audio|en-us-cacophony.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|cacophony|cacophonies}}

# A mix of discordant sounds; dissonance

===Antonyms===
*[[euphony]]
*[[harmony]]

